      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems from ASME V&V 10 or equivalent must confirm correct implementation of governing equations.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed against ASME V&V 10 benchmark suite for beam-bending and contact problems. Results match analytical solutions within 0.5%, confirming correct equation implementation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change <2% between successive refinements.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh convergence study conducted with three refinement levels (coarse, medium, fine). QoI change between medium and fine meshes: stiffness 0.7%, yield force 1.1%, force at 40 mm 0.9%. Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate discretization error bounds. Achieved level exceeds required."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals and energy balance must be monitored and documented to confirm numerical convergence.",
      "rationale": "Force and displacement residuals converged to below 1e-6 for all load steps. Energy balance error maintained below 0.1% throughout the analysis. Iterative solver settings documented and archived with model files."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments must be documented.",
      "rationale": "Model setup reviewed independently by a second analyst at FDA OSEL and by DePuy Synthes engineering team. Boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material assignments confirmed consistent with ASTM F1717 test configuration. No discrepancies identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form choices (constitutive laws, contact formulation, geometric representation) must be justified by literature or prior validation evidence.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive model justified for pre-yield regime; bilinear isotropic hardening applied for post-yield behavior based on published Ti-6Al-4V data. Penalty-based frictional contact (mu=0.2) consistent with prior pedicle screw validation studies. Geometric representation derived from CAD nominal dimensions confirmed against CMM measurements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters must be traceable to measured or certified sources with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E=114 GPa, yield strength=880 MPa) sourced from ASTM F136 certificate of conformance for the production lot used in bench testing. Geometric dimensions measured by CMM on three representative screws; mean values used with dimensional variability documented. UHMWPE block properties from supplier data sheet confirmed by independent tensile testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples must be representative of the intended clinical device and traceable to production specifications.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested, all drawn from production lots with full material and dimensional traceability. Constructs assembled per manufacturer IFU by trained personnel. Sample size sufficient to characterize inter-construct variability for the three QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must replicate or bracket the clinically relevant loading environment; multiple conditions preferred for Complete profile.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (5-degree offset block, quasi-static ramp to failure). Clinical loading encompasses a range of offset angles and dynamic components not represented in this single condition. Achieved level 1 (single standardized condition) falls below required level 2 for the Complete profile. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory precedent for F1717 as the standard acceptance test for spinal implant systems."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to the experimental test conditions used for validation.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in the FEA model directly replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry: fixed-base block, 5-degree offset upper block, displacement-controlled loading at the specified rate. Material properties matched to the certified lot used in bench testing. Dimensional inputs derived from CMM measurements of the same production lot. Equivalency confirmed by pre-test model-experiment comparison protocol."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E/uval) must be applied to all QoIs with pre-specified acceptance thresholds.",
      "rationale": "Three QoIs compared: construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. Pre-specified acceptance bounds: absolute percent difference <10% and E/uval <1.96. All three QoIs satisfied both criteria (E/uval: 0.84, 1.12, 1.41 respectively). Comparison conducted independently by FDA and DePuy Synthes analysts with consistent results."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs selected for validation must be directly linked to the clinical decision and the COU failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relevant to clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture, screw pullout, rod breakage). These QoIs map directly to the COU decision regarding structural adequacy of the pedicle screw system for lumbar fusion support."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be sufficiently similar to the COU in geometry, loading, and material to support extrapolation of credibility evidence.",
      "rationale": "Validation activity directly replicates the COU: same device geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), same loading mode (compression-bending per ASTM F1717), same material (Ti-6Al-4V), and same assembly configuration. No extrapolation across device families or loading modes required. Two-laboratory replication strengthens confidence in experimental reference data."
    }
  ],
