    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/fda-osel-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels for the Complete profile. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 1 against a required level 2; this gap is accepted given ASTM F1717 regulatory precedent and the medium model risk level. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified quantitative acceptance bounds (absolute difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). Two-laboratory replication and independent analyst review strengthen confidence. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under the stated COU.",
